There is, therefore, no real necessity for writing with Vahlen haec tot, on the analogy of Cic. pro Rosc. 32, 89 haec tot et tanta . . . quamdiu diceres.

Imagines ac tituli et statuae: As Aper is, speaking of novi homines sine commendatione natalium, imaqines cannot refer to the waxen images of ancestors, but rather to the so-called ‘clipeatae' or ‘argenteae imagines' which represented the Emperor or his amici or some distinguished man. Tituli were the inscriptions on these, hence joined by ac, i. e. imag. cum titulis et statuae.
